description: A One-of-a-Kind Waterfront Residence!! Welcome to Unit 404 at 33 Sleeper Street—where iconic views, architectural pedigree, and premium design meet in Boston’s hottest waterfront neighborhood. This two-bedroom, two-bath home offers front-row views of the Boston Tea Party Museum, Boston Harbor, and the city skyline. Overlooking the Rose Kennedy Greenway, the view is protected and permanent. INTERIOR Designed by Jeremiah Eck—New England Architectural Hall of Fame member and former Harvard Graduate School of Design lecturer—the condo blends industrial history with sharp, contemporary style. Exposed brick walls, glass block partitions, and perforated stainless steel create a clean, modern edge. The steel-and-glass shelving system adds both function and sculpture. Renovated by award-winning interior designer Lisa Hillson, the home features state-of-the-art appliances, electric shades, and thoughtful upgrades throughout.The layout includes a private sauna, two full bathrooms. and Laundry.
